  "texts": [
    "The pre-processing is conducted on four levels, i.e., character, word, n-gram, and sentence.",
    "Variant mapping and simplified: Currently, both simplified and traditional characters are used in different regions of China.",
    "In addition, the written form of ancient Chinese employs traditional characters, some of which have variants.",
    "To accommodate the",
    "Digital Text Metadata Index Info Variant Mapping N-gram Slicing Text Reuse Detection Hierarchical Doc Co-occurrence Diachronic N-gram Enhanced Browsing Frequency Count Retrieval Word Segmentation Simplified Data Labelling Data Pre-processing Raw Data Analysis Function Corpus Building Text Reuse Analysis word phrase sentence document word/n-gram query linguistic idiosyncrasies of diverse regions and map the variants, we used OpenCC 3 to transform all textual data into a consistent simplified format and store this copy."
